meaningMnemonic: You <radical>stand</radical> with another <radical>woman</radical> and, with your <radical>fingers</radical>, <kanji>adjoin</kanji> yourselves together. You are united, you are one.
readingMnemonic: All of the women who are now <kanji>adjoin</kanji>ing together are in <reading>sets</reading> (せつ). Sets of two, of course. One woman with another woman, standing in unison.
